WEBVTT

1
00:00:05.770 --> 00:00:07.423
All right. we're almost home.

2
00:00:23.613 --> 00:00:25.267
Whoa. calm down. boy.

3
00:00:25.354 --> 00:00:28.227
Whoa. whoa.

4
00:00:40.543 --> 00:00:42.415
It's right up here.

5
00:00:51.032 --> 00:00:53.208
You really think
it's worth 10 grand?

6
00:01:47.527 --> 00:01:49.224
Oh. my God.

7
00:01:49.311 --> 00:01:50.747
What?

8
00:01:50.878 --> 00:01:52.575
Remember Andrea McHugh?

9
00:01:52.662 --> 00:01:55.143
Blue mohawk. threw a brick
through a Starbucks window?

10
00:01:55.274 --> 00:01:57.363
The girl who stole a cop car
sophomore year?

11
00:01:57.406 --> 00:02:00.192
How could I forget?
- Yeah. look at this.

12
00:02:01.497 --> 00:02:06.154
- No way that's her.
# Blessed. #LiveLaughLove.

13
00:02:06.285 --> 00:02:09.027
Wow. so much for getting
out of small town life.

14
00:02:09.114 --> 00:02:11.594
- Seriously.
Three kids under five.

15
00:02:11.681 --> 00:02:13.292
That's a handful.

16
00:02:13.379 --> 00:02:15.859
Honey. if I ever suggest
coordinating sleepwear.

17
00:02:15.946 --> 00:02:18.166
you have permission to leave me
and take full custody.

18
00:02:18.210 --> 00:02:19.601
Honey. I would
not need permission.

19
00:02:19.689 --> 00:02:21.909
Oh.
that's what I love about you.

20
00:02:22.040 --> 00:02:23.128
My devastating charm?

21
00:02:23.258 --> 00:02:25.478
We both hate the same things.

22
00:02:28.611 --> 00:02:32.137
Oh. I might need the car today.

23
00:02:32.224 --> 00:02:35.749
Is it cool if I drive. and
I can just drop you at 26 Fed?

24
00:02:35.836 --> 00:02:37.968
- You know. you take the car.
I'll take the subway.

25
00:02:38.056 --> 00:02:40.188
What? You hate the subway.

26
00:02:40.275 --> 00:02:41.624
We both hate the subway.
See above.

27
00:02:41.711 --> 00:02:43.190
Yeah. fully aware. I just. uh.

28
00:02:43.235 --> 00:02:45.106
I actually have to go Uptown
today. so it'll be easier.

29
00:02:45.150 --> 00:02:46.368
Oh. what's Uptown?

30
00:02:48.109 --> 00:02:49.850
- This case.
I gotta talk to this guy.

31
00:02:49.980 --> 00:02:52.505
He's threatening
to recant his testimony.

32
00:02:52.592 --> 00:02:56.552
So Uptown I go.
- OK.

33
00:02:56.639 --> 00:02:58.337
What am I looking at. Malcolm?

34
00:02:58.424 --> 00:02:59.599
That's what I want to know.

35
00:02:59.729 --> 00:03:01.514
Something made
this crater last night.

36
00:03:01.601 --> 00:03:04.169
Radiation signatures consistent
with a power source.

37
00:03:04.212 --> 00:03:07.041
not a meteor. not debris.

38
00:03:07.128 --> 00:03:09.826
Something that was built.
- Can I see what's left of it?

39
00:03:09.913 --> 00:03:12.394
- That's just it.
Someone got here before us.

40
00:03:12.525 --> 00:03:15.397
Couple someones. actually.
One's in the morgue.

41
00:03:15.484 --> 00:03:18.835
And the other. well.
whatever made this crater.

42
00:03:18.966 --> 00:03:20.315
they've got it now.

43
00:03:20.402 --> 00:03:22.100
And we've checked with
everyone on our end.

44
00:03:22.187 --> 00:03:23.753
It wasn't Canadian.

45
00:03:23.840 --> 00:03:25.755
So?
- Are you asking if it's ours?

46
00:03:25.842 --> 00:03:26.887
Now that you mention it.

47
00:03:27.017 --> 00:03:28.236
Malcolm.
I'm finding out about this

48
00:03:28.323 --> 00:03:29.672
at the same time
that you're telling me.

49
00:03:29.803 --> 00:03:31.152
That's what you'd say
if itwas yours.

50
00:03:31.238 --> 00:03:34.373
And you're a good liar.
- Yes and yes.

51
00:03:34.460 --> 00:03:36.244
But in this case. it has
the advantage of being true.

52
00:03:36.331 --> 00:03:38.986
If this turns out to be
American technology

53
00:03:39.117 --> 00:03:40.683
that fell out of the sky...

54
00:03:40.770 --> 00:03:42.381
Malcolm.

55
00:03:42.468 --> 00:03:44.077
And you are now in
any way covering up.

56
00:03:44.122 --> 00:03:45.166
we're going to have
a serious problem.

57
00:03:46.646 --> 00:03:47.821
And I'm not someone that

58
00:03:47.908 --> 00:03:49.431
you want to have
a serious problem with.

59
00:03:49.518 --> 00:03:51.520
I thought Canadians
were supposed to be polite.

60
00:03:51.651 --> 00:03:53.696
That is an outdated
and offensive stereotype.

61
00:03:57.613 --> 00:04:00.094
All right.

62
00:04:00.225 --> 00:04:01.965
Let's gather the troops.
- Mm-hmm.

63
00:04:02.052 --> 00:04:04.620
So an unknown projectile
of unknown origin.

64
00:04:04.664 --> 00:04:07.057
with unknown payload.
emitting unknown amounts

65
00:04:07.145 --> 00:04:09.277
of deadly radiation.
is currently in unknown hands.

66
00:04:09.364 --> 00:04:11.932
Well. at least
we know our known unknowns.

67
00:04:12.019 --> 00:04:13.890
Whose is it?
Anyone call the lost and found?

68
00:04:14.021 --> 00:04:17.154
- Nobody's claimed it.
- Any ideas on what it is?

69
00:04:17.242 --> 00:04:18.808
It could be a weather balloon.

70
00:04:18.895 --> 00:04:20.723
Like the one the military
shot over South Carolina.

71
00:04:20.810 --> 00:04:21.942
courtesy of China?

72
00:04:22.029 --> 00:04:24.074
Or it could be a stealth drone.

73
00:04:24.162 --> 00:04:25.467
meaning one of ours.

74
00:04:25.598 --> 00:04:28.035
Meaning an illegal U.S.-run
surveillance program.

75
00:04:28.166 --> 00:04:29.167
More like unsanctioned.

76
00:04:29.254 --> 00:04:30.951
We don't like labels
here at the CIA.

77
00:04:31.080 --> 00:04:32.866
If it is ours.
we've just stumbled

78
00:04:32.909 --> 00:04:35.521
onto a massive diplomatic
incident with Canada.

79
00:04:35.651 --> 00:04:37.610
- Well. there...
there is another possibility.

80
00:04:37.697 --> 00:04:39.306
I mean. the...
the radiation signatures

81
00:04:39.394 --> 00:04:42.484
are inconsistent with standard
propulsion and electronics.

82
00:04:42.615 --> 00:04:43.833
Please don't say aliens.

83
00:04:43.920 --> 00:04:45.183
With the amount of energy output

84
00:04:45.313 --> 00:04:48.055
these things are emitting.
I mean. it... it... it...

85
00:04:49.143 --> 00:04:52.320
It's probably not aliens.
That's... that's what I'm saying.

86
00:04:52.451 --> 00:04:53.495
Whatever caused that crater.

87
00:04:53.626 --> 00:04:55.193
we need to find out who took it.

88
00:04:55.323 --> 00:04:57.412
If it was ours
and it's been recovered.

89
00:04:57.499 --> 00:04:59.284
it's embarrassing.
but it's contained.

90
00:04:59.371 --> 00:05:01.503
Yeah. but if someone
got there first.

91
00:05:01.590 --> 00:05:03.026
it could already be
on the black market.

92
00:05:03.113 --> 00:05:04.463
I'll make some calls.

93
00:05:04.506 --> 00:05:05.986
I'll try my government contacts.

94
00:05:06.116 --> 00:05:08.815
And let's bring in Kevin Turner
from Counter Terrorism.

95
00:05:25.179 --> 00:05:28.748
I think I found
what made your crater.

96
00:05:28.878 --> 00:05:31.229
Where did you get these?

97
00:05:31.316 --> 00:05:33.187
Would you believe me if
I said they fell off a truck?

98
00:05:33.318 --> 00:05:38.236
Must have been a weird truck.

99
00:05:38.366 --> 00:05:40.977
Looks like a low Earth
orbit satellite.

100
00:05:41.064 --> 00:05:44.372
Most of it burned up. but
that core was built to survive.

101
00:05:44.503 --> 00:05:47.201
Whose is it.
if you had to guess?

102
00:05:47.288 --> 00:05:49.986
Russian. Chinese. Indian. maybe.

103
00:05:50.073 --> 00:05:51.510
What's it matter?

104
00:05:54.774 --> 00:05:56.123
I have a team out in the field

105
00:05:56.210 --> 00:05:58.343
trying to secure this thing.

106
00:05:58.430 --> 00:06:00.562
I don't know who
they might bump into.

107
00:06:00.693 --> 00:06:03.652
I'll look into it.
see if I can track it.

108
00:06:03.739 --> 00:06:06.351
figure out who launched it.

109
00:06:11.356 --> 00:06:12.922
You told Katie
you're going Uptown

110
00:06:13.009 --> 00:06:14.576
because a witness is
recanting their testimony?

111
00:06:14.663 --> 00:06:16.099
It was the first thing
I could think of.

112
00:06:16.186 --> 00:06:17.797
Jeez. mate. less is more.

113
00:06:17.927 --> 00:06:19.233
It's the details
that trip you up.

114
00:06:19.320 --> 00:06:20.321
Have you still not told her

115
00:06:20.365 --> 00:06:21.496
you're working
for the fusion cell?

116
00:06:21.583 --> 00:06:22.758
I don't want her
worrying about me.

117
00:06:22.802 --> 00:06:25.152
She's a worrier.
I hate lying to her.

118
00:06:25.239 --> 00:06:26.414
Well. you'll get used to it.

119
00:06:26.545 --> 00:06:28.851
Yeah. that's what
I'm worried about.

120
00:06:28.982 --> 00:06:29.939
This is her.

121
00:06:29.983 --> 00:06:31.941
Sixth sense. every time.

122
00:06:32.028 --> 00:06:33.160
All right. well. take it.

123
00:06:33.247 --> 00:06:34.117
I'll only be
a couple of minutes.

124
00:06:34.161 --> 00:06:37.382
And less is more.
- Yeah.

125
00:06:38.731 --> 00:06:40.298
Hey. honey.

126
00:06:40.385 --> 00:06:42.343
Yeah. I just got Uptown.
What's up?

127
00:06:57.358 --> 00:06:59.839
You're looking for Nigel.

128
00:06:59.926 --> 00:07:01.101
- Yeah.
Is he in?

129
00:07:01.188 --> 00:07:04.322
Blew his ACL. pickleball.

130
00:07:04.452 --> 00:07:06.411
- Vicious sport.
I told him to stick to chess.

131
00:07:06.541 --> 00:07:09.196
- Yeah.
Something I can help you with?

132
00:07:09.283 --> 00:07:12.155
Uh. it's a very
particular request.

133
00:07:12.199 --> 00:07:13.592
I normally just deal with him.

134
00:07:13.635 --> 00:07:16.551
- Mm.
Try me.

135
00:07:16.638 --> 00:07:19.119
OK.

136
00:07:19.249 --> 00:07:22.601
Where can I find a copy of
Chekhov's "The Burial Mound"?

137
00:07:22.688 --> 00:07:26.779
Neverland. maybe.
or the lost city of Atlantis.

138
00:07:26.909 --> 00:07:29.782
It doesn't exist.

139
00:07:29.869 --> 00:07:32.219
All right.
how about "Ben-Hur." 1933.

140
00:07:32.306 --> 00:07:34.003
first Modern Library edition?

141
00:07:44.231 --> 00:07:47.060
Someone must have misplaced it.

142
00:07:47.147 --> 00:07:49.758
Now you can put up
your sneaky little bat signal

143
00:07:49.845 --> 00:07:52.457
to whoever the hell you're
trying to communicate with.

144
00:07:52.587 --> 00:07:54.328
Thank you.

145
00:07:54.415 --> 00:07:55.938
Evelyn.

146
00:07:56.025 --> 00:07:58.158
But like I said.
I might not be here next time.

147
00:07:58.245 --> 00:08:03.163
So this electricity
crackling between us...

148
00:08:03.250 --> 00:08:04.599
Don't get used to it.

149
00:08:19.135 --> 00:08:20.180
Our mystery item.

150
00:08:20.267 --> 00:08:21.964
A satellite fell out of orbit.

151
00:08:22.051 --> 00:08:23.705
Most of it burned up
upon re-entry

152
00:08:23.792 --> 00:08:25.751
or shattered into fragments.
except the battery.

153
00:08:25.794 --> 00:08:27.579
Most satellites are
powered by solar panels.

154
00:08:27.709 --> 00:08:30.320
This one was powered
by an enriched cesium core.

155
00:08:30.408 --> 00:08:32.497
- A nuclear battery.
- Yeah.

156
00:08:32.584 --> 00:08:35.629
So you're saying somebody
put a nuclear device in space?

157
00:08:35.717 --> 00:08:38.416
Cesium-137. to be precise.

158
00:08:38.546 --> 00:08:41.680
So you're aware cesium-137
has roughly ten half-lives

159
00:08:41.767 --> 00:08:44.944
before its radioactivity
diminishes to safe levels?

160
00:08:46.685 --> 00:08:48.904
Sorry. in layman's terms.
that simply means that it's a...

161
00:08:48.991 --> 00:08:51.559
Dirty bomb with that material
could irradiate Times Square

162
00:08:51.603 --> 00:08:53.779
for 300 years. give or take.
- Yes. exactly.

163
00:08:53.909 --> 00:08:54.736
Certainly. as you can imagine.

164
00:08:54.867 --> 00:08:55.998
there are plenty
of terror groups

165
00:08:56.085 --> 00:08:56.999
who'd love
to get their hands on it.

166
00:08:57.130 --> 00:08:58.261
Rogue nations too.

167
00:08:58.348 --> 00:08:59.785
Do we know who sent it up?

168
00:08:59.872 --> 00:09:01.569
That's not exactly
my department.

169
00:09:04.137 --> 00:09:05.791
There are over 13.000
satellites in orbit

170
00:09:05.921 --> 00:09:08.533
operated by 80 countries.
It might take me just a minute.

171
00:09:08.620 --> 00:09:11.231
You're doing great.

172
00:09:11.361 --> 00:09:12.754
Colin. any word
from your contacts?

173
00:09:12.885 --> 00:09:13.755
No. not yet.

174
00:09:13.886 --> 00:09:14.930
But let's hope he gets in touch

175
00:09:15.017 --> 00:09:17.324
before this thing
hits the open market.

176
00:10:16.557 --> 00:10:17.819
Nice place you got here.

177
00:10:21.127 --> 00:10:23.346
Excellent bourbon.

178
00:10:23.433 --> 00:10:25.479
Jonah.

179
00:10:25.523 --> 00:10:28.047
You got my signal. then?
- I did.

180
00:10:28.134 --> 00:10:30.876
And I believe I have something
you're looking for.

181
00:10:40.575 --> 00:10:42.752
So what. you're an amateur
photographer now. are you?

182
00:10:42.839 --> 00:10:44.623
I'm thinking about
turning professional.

183
00:10:44.710 --> 00:10:46.146
Who's your friend?

184
00:10:46.190 --> 00:10:48.105
Fellow literature enthusiast.

185
00:10:48.192 --> 00:10:50.194
Ah. looks like a Fed.

186
00:10:50.281 --> 00:10:51.456
How's retirement?

187
00:10:51.499 --> 00:10:54.154
Boring.

188
00:10:54.241 --> 00:10:56.853
I even considered starting
a war to pass the time.

189
00:10:56.983 --> 00:10:59.638
- I thought you liked wars.
- I like war profiteering.

190
00:10:59.725 --> 00:11:01.118
And right now it sounds like

191
00:11:01.161 --> 00:11:04.730
you have a very expensive
problem on your hands.

192
00:11:04.774 --> 00:11:06.297
What have you heard?

193
00:11:06.384 --> 00:11:09.387
Nuclear-powered satellite
scattered across Nova Scotia.

194
00:11:09.517 --> 00:11:11.258
but the battery's missing.

195
00:11:11.345 --> 00:11:13.565
with enough cesium
to level ten city blocks.

196
00:11:13.696 --> 00:11:17.090
The seller.
the one who found it.

197
00:11:17.221 --> 00:11:18.701
is Mateo Kola.

198
00:11:20.615 --> 00:11:22.226
Albanian organized crime.

199
00:11:22.313 --> 00:11:24.402
Controls much of the
smuggling in Eastern Canada.

200
00:11:24.489 --> 00:11:28.406
Some local found the battery.
contacted Mateo for a payday.

201
00:11:28.536 --> 00:11:31.191
he killed her.
and grabbed it for himself.

202
00:11:31.322 --> 00:11:33.890
Well. I always admire
an entrepreneur.

203
00:11:34.020 --> 00:11:35.326
He has a network here
in New York.

204
00:11:35.413 --> 00:11:38.546
He's looking for a buyer to
take it off his hands tomorrow

205
00:11:38.633 --> 00:11:41.636
at the low. low price
of $50 million.

206
00:11:41.724 --> 00:11:43.769
- Oh. is that all?
Bargain.

207
00:11:43.900 --> 00:11:46.337
Any chatter on Telegram.
Discord?

208
00:11:46.424 --> 00:11:47.555
Usual suspects.

209
00:11:47.599 --> 00:11:50.341
Terrorists. rogue states.

210
00:11:50.428 --> 00:11:52.778
some hedge fund guy
in Montana with a bunker.

211
00:11:52.909 --> 00:11:54.258
Nuclear is the new black. eh?

212
00:11:54.388 --> 00:11:55.912
But no one with the ability

213
00:11:55.999 --> 00:11:58.436
to pull together
that kind of cash so quickly.

214
00:12:00.090 --> 00:12:02.179
Oh. right.

215
00:12:02.266 --> 00:12:03.658
Now I know why you
skipped the phone call

216
00:12:03.789 --> 00:12:05.225
and made
the personal appearance.

217
00:12:05.356 --> 00:12:08.620
Well. the CIA does have
a long and. uh...

218
00:12:08.707 --> 00:12:13.581
storied history of overpaying.

219
00:12:13.668 --> 00:12:16.280
I'd love nothing more
than to simply

220
00:12:16.410 --> 00:12:17.498
make the introduction

221
00:12:17.629 --> 00:12:20.458
and help you take it
off the market.

222
00:12:22.199 --> 00:12:23.940
I think it's a solid plan.

223
00:12:24.070 --> 00:12:25.593
It's a lot of money
for the U.S. government

224
00:12:25.680 --> 00:12:27.595
to be throwing at
an ex-cop-turned-arms-dealer.

225
00:12:27.682 --> 00:12:29.510
- OK. fine.
Jonah Le'Roux is a drunk.

226
00:12:29.597 --> 00:12:30.684
And he is a shifty bastard.

227
00:12:30.773 --> 00:12:33.297
But when money's involved.
he's reliable.

228
00:12:33.427 --> 00:12:34.907
What other choice
do we have. Nikki?

229
00:12:35.038 --> 00:12:36.822
If a terrorist group get their
hands on this nuclear battery...

230
00:12:36.909 --> 00:12:38.389
The seller. Mateo Kola.

231
00:12:38.476 --> 00:12:40.695
known for making
undercover agents disappear.

232
00:12:40.783 --> 00:12:42.523
I can maintain my cover.

233
00:12:42.654 --> 00:12:43.524
We know where Mateo
is going to be

234
00:12:43.611 --> 00:12:45.265
when the sale is happening.

235
00:12:45.352 --> 00:12:47.354
Why not give Jonah
the courtesy of a finder's fee

236
00:12:47.441 --> 00:12:49.487
and send the Nuclear
Emergency Support Team

237
00:12:49.574 --> 00:12:51.228
to recover the battery?

238
00:12:51.315 --> 00:12:52.142
We can't involve NEST.

239
00:12:52.229 --> 00:12:53.447
we can't involve other agencies.

240
00:12:53.491 --> 00:12:55.232
not until we have the nuke
in our possession.

241
00:12:55.275 --> 00:12:56.450
We've got to be delicate
about this.

242
00:12:56.537 --> 00:12:58.452
You can't hunt truffles
with a backhoe.

243
00:12:58.539 --> 00:13:00.715
Just to be clear. you're the
truffle pig in this metaphor.

244
00:13:00.803 --> 00:13:03.109
It is a volatile
nuclear battery.

245
00:13:03.196 --> 00:13:05.024
- NEST uses precision.
- We go in with weapons hot...

246
00:13:05.068 --> 00:13:06.765
- I'm totally confident.
I have no doubt.

247
00:13:06.852 --> 00:13:09.289
Colin's right.

248
00:13:09.376 --> 00:13:12.423
The only way to get eyes on
the device is to stage a buy.

249
00:13:12.510 --> 00:13:15.252
The only way to do that
is with Colin's asset.

250
00:13:15.339 --> 00:13:17.080
It's the safest way to get
Mateo to produce the nuke.

251
00:13:17.210 --> 00:13:19.517
Let us do that. then send NEST
in to make the recovery.

252
00:13:26.872 --> 00:13:28.613
I like it.

253
00:13:28.700 --> 00:13:30.441
Oh. that's all it takes. is it?

254
00:13:30.528 --> 00:13:31.659
Bill signs off and we're a go?

255
00:13:31.790 --> 00:13:35.141
Just take the win.

256
00:13:35.228 --> 00:13:36.751
Walk me through it
one more time.

257
00:13:36.839 --> 00:13:37.970
OK.

258
00:13:40.799 --> 00:13:43.758
I'll check into the hotel
as Joel Andrews. the buyer.

259
00:13:43.889 --> 00:13:46.109
a bagman for a rogue nation
trying to level up.

260
00:13:46.239 --> 00:13:47.153
And Bill?

261
00:13:47.240 --> 00:13:48.546
Bill will be my muscle.

262
00:13:48.676 --> 00:13:49.982
Me personally. I thought
I could have pulled off

263
00:13:50.069 --> 00:13:51.288
international
terrorist financier.

264
00:13:51.331 --> 00:13:53.899
but you know how he gets.

265
00:13:53.986 --> 00:13:55.335
Jonah will be there
as my broker.

266
00:13:55.422 --> 00:13:57.250
He'll make the introduction
to Mateo at the set time.

267
00:13:57.381 --> 00:13:58.948
Joel Andrews.

268
00:13:59.035 --> 00:14:00.253
And how do you
check the merchandise?

269
00:14:00.340 --> 00:14:01.515
I mean. you can't exactly

270
00:14:01.602 --> 00:14:02.908
check the tires
on nuclear material.

271
00:14:02.995 --> 00:14:04.301
That's why I'm taking
my science advisor.

272
00:14:06.725 --> 00:14:08.117
You want to bring Gina
on the op?

273
00:14:08.248 --> 00:14:09.510
She's an analyst.

274
00:14:09.597 --> 00:14:10.772
She's the only one of us
who knows the difference

275
00:14:10.903 --> 00:14:12.731
between a nuclear reactor
and a hair dryer.

276
00:14:12.774 --> 00:14:13.732
I need her in the field on this.

277
00:14:13.819 --> 00:14:15.211
Thank you.

278
00:14:15.342 --> 00:14:16.517
OK. but at the
first sign of danger.

279
00:14:16.604 --> 00:14:18.127
I'm sending in reinforcements.

280
00:14:18.214 --> 00:14:20.608
And I'd expect nothing less.

281
00:14:24.804 --> 00:14:26.588
Any trends I should know about?

282
00:14:26.675 --> 00:14:28.329
Faux suede is coming back.

283
00:14:28.460 --> 00:14:29.678
I didn't realize it ever left.

284
00:14:33.073 --> 00:14:36.381
Mateo's leaving the hotel.

285
00:14:36.511 --> 00:14:38.557
He might be going
to retrieve the battery.

286
00:14:38.687 --> 00:14:39.993
We need ears in his room

287
00:14:40.124 --> 00:14:41.168
so we know when
he brings it back in.

288
00:14:41.299 --> 00:14:42.953
There's no way he'd leave
his room unattended.

289
00:14:43.040 --> 00:14:44.737
We could bug the room next door.

290
00:14:44.824 --> 00:14:46.260
Directional mic in the vent?

291
00:14:46.347 --> 00:14:47.479
Sorry. for a moment there.

292
00:14:47.566 --> 00:14:48.828
I thought
my comms stopped working.

293
00:14:48.915 --> 00:14:50.569
'cause you actually
sounded like a spy. Bill.

294
00:14:54.399 --> 00:14:56.923
I can go to the front desk.
get his room number.

295
00:14:57.010 --> 00:14:58.533
Zeeb said
he would hack the system.

296
00:14:58.577 --> 00:14:59.534
Yeah. that's gonna
take 30 minutes.

297
00:14:59.665 --> 00:15:01.058
I can do it in two.

298
00:15:11.111 --> 00:15:13.200
What are you doing?

299
00:15:17.465 --> 00:15:18.727
OK. fine.

300
00:15:18.858 --> 00:15:21.382
I'm excited to be
out in the field.

301
00:15:21.469 --> 00:15:23.732
Three years running background
checks and threat assessments.

302
00:15:23.819 --> 00:15:24.995
What do you expect?

303
00:15:25.082 --> 00:15:27.171
Eh. let her work.

304
00:15:27.258 --> 00:15:29.303
OK.

305
00:15:29.390 --> 00:15:32.350
One slip. that's all it takes.

306
00:15:32.393 --> 00:15:35.353
And it's not always you
that pays.

307
00:15:49.802 --> 00:15:51.717
Ugh. damn it. Mateo.
where are you?

308
00:15:51.804 --> 00:15:53.110
I drove all the way up here

309
00:15:53.197 --> 00:15:53.980
and you don't even
answer the phone?

310
00:15:54.024 --> 00:15:55.939
What am I supposed to do?

311
00:15:56.026 --> 00:15:58.985
It's like you have
no respect for me at all.

312
00:15:59.072 --> 00:16:01.031
You know what? Whatever.
I don't even care.

313
00:16:01.161 --> 00:16:04.208
I hope that you're having
a great time.

314
00:16:04.295 --> 00:16:07.689
- Are you all right. miss?
- Oh. my God.

315
00:16:07.776 --> 00:16:09.256
I am so sorry.

316
00:16:09.343 --> 00:16:11.693
I'm just...
I'm looking for my boyfriend.

317
00:16:11.824 --> 00:16:12.999
Boyfriend. boyfriend.

318
00:16:13.086 --> 00:16:14.827
I'm just...
I'm one of many. actually.

319
00:16:14.914 --> 00:16:17.569
So...

320
00:16:17.656 --> 00:16:19.484
You know. he must... he must
have checked in already.

321
00:16:19.614 --> 00:16:21.790
Maybe you can help me
find his room?

322
00:16:21.834 --> 00:16:23.488
Mateo Kola?

323
00:16:23.575 --> 00:16:25.272
Well. I'm really
not supposed to.

324
00:16:25.403 --> 00:16:26.970
I know you guys
have all these rules.

325
00:16:27.057 --> 00:16:28.580
and you look like you're
really good at your job.

326
00:16:28.710 --> 00:16:31.887
It's just...
- Mm-hmm.

327
00:16:33.933 --> 00:16:36.718
All right.

328
00:16:43.899 --> 00:16:45.553
Oh. my God. you are a lifesaver.

329
00:16:45.597 --> 00:16:48.295
Thank you.

330
00:16:51.037 --> 00:16:52.996
Poor bastard
never stood a chance.

331
00:17:08.967 --> 00:17:10.969
Maintenance.

332
00:17:11.056 --> 00:17:12.752
You called the front desk.

333
00:17:12.884 --> 00:17:15.582
You smelled gas or something
coming from your vents?

334
00:17:15.669 --> 00:17:17.758
That wasn't me.

335
00:17:17.889 --> 00:17:20.847
- Oh. oh. sorry.
Next suite. My bad.

336
00:17:20.934 --> 00:17:25.505
Wait. uh. maybe you should
check mine too. just in case.

337
00:17:27.333 --> 00:17:30.989
All right. yeah.
it'll only take a minute.

338
00:17:31.076 --> 00:17:32.208
He'll give it a once-over.

339
00:17:32.295 --> 00:17:33.426
- All right.
- Should be good to go.

340
00:17:33.513 --> 00:17:34.427
You haven't smelled
any gas. have you?

341
00:17:34.558 --> 00:17:35.994
I have not. no.

342
00:17:36.081 --> 00:17:37.561
Yeah. I don't smell
anything either.

343
00:17:37.691 --> 00:17:38.736
so you probably should be good.

344
00:17:38.823 --> 00:17:40.868
Yeah. yeah. I appreciate it.

345
00:17:40.955 --> 00:17:42.000
Well. that's grand.

346
00:17:42.087 --> 00:17:43.567
Hey. our goal is just to try

347
00:17:43.697 --> 00:17:45.090
and keep everyone safe
here today.

348
00:17:45.221 --> 00:17:46.657
Mm. yeah. appreciate it.

349
00:17:46.744 --> 00:17:48.311
Yeah. well. let us know
if you smell anything.

350
00:17:48.398 --> 00:17:49.486
All right. thanks
for checking. gentlemen.

351
00:17:49.573 --> 00:17:51.357
- Yeah. take care. buddy.
- You too. now.

352
00:17:51.488 --> 00:17:52.663
That should catch all the audio

353
00:17:52.706 --> 00:17:54.230
in Mateo's room.

354
00:17:54.317 --> 00:17:55.927
Like I said. keep it simple.

355
00:17:56.014 --> 00:17:57.798
- Hey. guys.
I can't find Jonah.

356
00:17:57.885 --> 00:17:59.322
What?

357
00:17:59.409 --> 00:18:00.279
I thought he was posted
at the back door.

358
00:18:00.323 --> 00:18:01.759
- And you checked...
- Everywhere.

359
00:18:01.802 --> 00:18:02.890
Even the men's restroom.

360
00:18:02.977 --> 00:18:04.457
Definitely got some
interesting looks there.

361
00:18:04.544 --> 00:18:06.155
I knew we shouldn't
have trusted this guy.

362
00:18:06.242 --> 00:18:08.592
Just go back to the room.
wait there.

363
00:18:08.679 --> 00:18:11.551
I'll take the stairs up
and check the top two floors.

364
00:18:11.595 --> 00:18:13.031
I'll check the bar downstairs.

365
00:18:13.118 --> 00:18:14.685
if he's a drunk like you say.

366
00:19:00.796 --> 00:19:02.841
- Hey. Any sign of Jonah?
- No. Where's Bill?

367
00:19:02.929 --> 00:19:05.061
- I don't know.
His comms have dropped out.

368
00:19:05.192 --> 00:19:06.628
I'm supposed to be meeting
Mateo in his room any minute.

369
00:19:06.715 --> 00:19:08.108
and we've got no one
to make the introduction.

370
00:19:08.195 --> 00:19:09.370
I thought you said
Jonah was reliable.

371
00:19:09.413 --> 00:19:10.980
Please don't quote me.

372
00:19:11.111 --> 00:19:13.069
OK. we need to find them now.

373
00:19:13.200 --> 00:19:14.984
This thing's gone pear-shaped
before it even started.

374
00:19:22.252 --> 00:19:24.211
Who do you work for?

375
00:19:32.741 --> 00:19:34.525
Where did you come from. huh?

376
00:19:34.612 --> 00:19:36.179
Where... where do
any of us come from?

377
00:19:36.310 --> 00:19:37.354
You know.
when you think about it?

378
00:19:38.834 --> 00:19:39.922
Whoa. whoa. whoa!

379
00:19:40.009 --> 00:19:43.491
I need him alive.

380
00:19:48.322 --> 00:19:50.889
All right. gentlemen. you.
uh. relax. get some vitamin D.

381
00:19:51.020 --> 00:19:53.544
I'll be back.
And when I do...

382
00:19:53.631 --> 00:19:55.546
you better tell me
everything you know.

383
00:20:03.772 --> 00:20:05.034
Those friends of yours?

384
00:20:05.078 --> 00:20:06.340
I have no idea
who those guys were.

385
00:20:06.427 --> 00:20:07.906
but I knew they'd make you.

386
00:20:07.994 --> 00:20:09.169
I bet you they made you

387
00:20:09.212 --> 00:20:11.127
before you brushed your teeth
this morning.

388
00:20:11.214 --> 00:20:12.868
When you were born.
I bet the doctor said.

389
00:20:12.999 --> 00:20:15.697
look at this perfectly healthy
little federal agent.

390
00:20:17.307 --> 00:20:19.222
Oh. God.

391
00:20:19.295 --> 00:20:21.210
What. did you forget
you were a cop?

392
00:20:21.311 --> 00:20:24.010
Yeah. I was. until
people like you burned me.

393
00:20:25.359 --> 00:20:28.144
Yeah. maybe don't take bribes
next time.

394
00:20:31.104 --> 00:20:33.106
Whoa. whoa. whoa.
What are you doing?

395
00:20:33.193 --> 00:20:35.064
What's it look like I'm doing?

396
00:20:35.108 --> 00:20:37.066
I'm going to take them out
when they come back.

397
00:20:37.153 --> 00:20:38.981
- Are you crazy?
What. with IKEA leftovers?

398
00:20:39.068 --> 00:20:40.243
They have guns.
They will kill us.

399
00:20:40.374 --> 00:20:41.592
They would have done it already.

400
00:20:41.679 --> 00:20:43.464
They want to break us.

401
00:20:43.507 --> 00:20:45.727
- Yeah. but they won't.
- Yeah. speak for yourself.

402
00:20:45.814 --> 00:20:47.816
And it's going to hurt
like hell when they try.

403
00:20:47.903 --> 00:20:49.296
We gotta get out of here.

404
00:20:54.910 --> 00:20:56.912
Hey.

405
00:20:56.999 --> 00:20:59.306
We can escape out the vent.

406
00:21:02.483 --> 00:21:04.659
You going to help me or what?

407
00:21:07.357 --> 00:21:09.098
Well. they couldn't
have just vanished.

408
00:21:09.185 --> 00:21:10.056
They got to be somewhere
at the hotel.

409
00:21:10.186 --> 00:21:11.405
Have Zeeb see if he can access

410
00:21:11.492 --> 00:21:12.928
the hotel security cameras.

411
00:21:13.015 --> 00:21:14.625
OK. good idea.

412
00:21:14.712 --> 00:21:17.541
What if someone took them?

413
00:21:17.672 --> 00:21:18.760
Well. if they did.

414
00:21:18.890 --> 00:21:20.718
it means they want this thing
more than we do.

415
00:21:20.762 --> 00:21:22.068
And that means. Colin.

416
00:21:22.155 --> 00:21:24.635
that we need you
to approach Mateo now.

417
00:21:24.722 --> 00:21:26.420
Without Jonah there
to make an introduction?

418
00:21:26.507 --> 00:21:27.725
Well. he doesn't know me
from Adam.

419
00:21:27.856 --> 00:21:28.944
Make it work.

420
00:21:28.987 --> 00:21:30.119
Get the battery
and get out of there.

421
00:21:30.250 --> 00:21:31.903
I could pretend to be Jonah.

422
00:21:32.034 --> 00:21:33.688
Won't Mateo be looking for...

423
00:21:33.731 --> 00:21:35.472
- What?
A man?

424
00:21:35.516 --> 00:21:37.083
They don't know what Jonah is.

425
00:21:37.170 --> 00:21:39.041
We put a bug in their room.
Mateo was talking to his guys.

426
00:21:39.128 --> 00:21:40.477
We know they've never met.

427
00:21:40.564 --> 00:21:43.437
They only ever communicated
over encrypted texts.

428
00:21:43.567 --> 00:21:45.787
Jonah could be a woman.
he could be a man.

429
00:21:45.874 --> 00:21:48.964
or a string quartet.

430
00:21:50.792 --> 00:21:54.448
I didn't join the CIA
to sit on the bench.

431
00:21:54.535 --> 00:21:56.580
OK.

432
00:21:56.711 --> 00:21:58.669
Go with the flow.

433
00:21:58.756 --> 00:22:00.845
But it's Colin's flow.
You understand?

434
00:22:03.065 --> 00:22:04.936
- Seen. not heard.
Got it.

435
00:22:07.939 --> 00:22:11.160
All right.
if anything turns in that room.

436
00:22:11.247 --> 00:22:13.380
you follow my cues
and you walk away. OK?

437
00:22:13.467 --> 00:22:15.382
Promise.

438
00:22:15.512 --> 00:22:17.732
Put your glasses on.

439
00:22:43.018 --> 00:22:44.759
- All right.
- OK.

440
00:22:44.846 --> 00:22:46.630
Want to buy me a drink first?

441
00:22:46.761 --> 00:22:48.893
We were told the meeting
was 2:00 p.m.

442
00:22:48.980 --> 00:22:50.243
Who are you?

443
00:23:03.560 --> 00:23:08.739
Joel Andrews.
Andrews Investments.

444
00:23:08.870 --> 00:23:10.611
And her?

445
00:23:10.741 --> 00:23:12.656
Who do you think I am?

446
00:23:12.743 --> 00:23:14.484
I'm Jonah.

447
00:23:17.705 --> 00:23:20.273
You're Jonah?

448
00:23:20.403 --> 00:23:22.710
Sometimes I'm Jonah.
sometimes I'm Ashley.

449
00:23:22.797 --> 00:23:25.103
You must be Mateo.

450
00:23:25.234 --> 00:23:27.497
OK. now we're done
playing 20 questions.

451
00:23:27.628 --> 00:23:30.587
Can we get to
the business in hand?

452
00:23:30.718 --> 00:23:32.589
Where's the nuke?

453
00:23:32.720 --> 00:23:36.245
You think I'm stupid enough
to have it in the room?

454
00:23:36.332 --> 00:23:40.641
I need to see
proof of funds first.

455
00:23:40.728 --> 00:23:43.644
You show me yours.
and I'll show you mine.

456
00:23:54.742 --> 00:23:57.745
There. good enough?

457
00:23:57.875 --> 00:24:00.182
Now where's my nuke?

458
00:24:00.269 --> 00:24:04.317
Patience. patience.

459
00:24:04.404 --> 00:24:08.103
I haven't heard from the
other interested parties yet.

460
00:24:08.146 --> 00:24:09.757
- Hold on.
Other interested parties?

461
00:24:09.887 --> 00:24:11.062
That wasn't the plan.

462
00:24:11.149 --> 00:24:15.806
Plans change.
just like the price.

463
00:24:15.893 --> 00:24:18.156
It's going up.

464
00:24:18.244 --> 00:24:19.462
Is it?

465
00:24:29.429 --> 00:24:30.734
Are we getting
into a bidding war?

466
00:24:30.865 --> 00:24:31.822
Sounds like it.

467
00:24:31.909 --> 00:24:33.389
What are we going to do?

468
00:24:33.476 --> 00:24:34.912
I mean. there's no way we have
enough for best and final.

469
00:24:34.999 --> 00:24:36.697
That's for Nikki to sort out
with Headquarters.

470
00:24:36.784 --> 00:24:38.002
So what do you think?

471
00:24:38.133 --> 00:24:39.569
You think Jonah
walked us into a trap?

472
00:24:39.613 --> 00:24:40.657
It's the first thing
I'm going to ask him

473
00:24:40.788 --> 00:24:42.137
when we find him.

474
00:24:48.796 --> 00:24:51.973
So how'd you end up
on the other side?

475
00:24:52.103 --> 00:24:53.757
I was the cop
on the brochure. you know?

476
00:24:53.888 --> 00:24:55.803
For the first three years.

477
00:24:55.890 --> 00:24:59.110
Wife. four kids on a cop's
salary. you know the deal.

478
00:24:59.197 --> 00:25:02.026
- Oh. it's a real sob story.
- You want to hear it or not?

479
00:25:02.157 --> 00:25:03.898
And not that
this excuses anything.

480
00:25:03.985 --> 00:25:05.508
but everybody was doing it.

481
00:25:05.595 --> 00:25:07.249
Look the other way
for a local dealer.

482
00:25:07.336 --> 00:25:09.077
suddenly. there's food
on the table.

483
00:25:09.164 --> 00:25:10.339
presents under
the Christmas tree.

484
00:25:10.383 --> 00:25:11.906
no one gets hurt.

485
00:25:11.993 --> 00:25:15.170
You could give up this life.
still get your family back.

486
00:25:15.257 --> 00:25:18.913
No. Because... and my wife.
she knew this too...

487
00:25:19.000 --> 00:25:20.523
I liked it.

488
00:25:20.610 --> 00:25:22.482
The money?

489
00:25:22.569 --> 00:25:24.222
The danger.

490
00:25:24.353 --> 00:25:26.529
The never knowing
if I'd make it out alive.

491
00:25:26.616 --> 00:25:29.271
The rush when I did.
And you like it too.

492
00:25:29.358 --> 00:25:31.926
- No.
No. I'm nothing like that.

493
00:25:32.013 --> 00:25:33.319
Oh. yeah.

494
00:25:33.362 --> 00:25:36.104
OK. you have a woman
back at home?

495
00:25:36.191 --> 00:25:39.673
A wife?
- A fiancée.

496
00:25:39.760 --> 00:25:41.892
- OK.
So you're playing with fire.

497
00:25:41.979 --> 00:25:44.373
You couldwork a desk job.
coach the soccer team.

498
00:25:44.460 --> 00:25:45.766
be home for dinner.

499
00:25:45.853 --> 00:25:47.594
Instead. you chose to be here
risking everything

500
00:25:47.724 --> 00:25:50.292
while she's back at home
thinking everything is fine

501
00:25:50.423 --> 00:25:52.425
until one day.
she gets a phone call

502
00:25:52.555 --> 00:25:55.297
saying that
you're not coming home.

503
00:25:55.428 --> 00:25:57.952
You're trying to have it
both ways. suit.

504
00:25:58.039 --> 00:26:00.824
And let me tell you you can't.

505
00:26:12.619 --> 00:26:14.577
Finally.
- Oh. yeah.

506
00:26:28.025 --> 00:26:29.810
- OK.
- I think we got it.

507
00:26:42.039 --> 00:26:43.606
Ah. damn it.

508
00:26:46.087 --> 00:26:48.263
Now what?

509
00:26:55.357 --> 00:26:57.228
OK. thanks.

510
00:26:57.315 --> 00:26:58.795
Nikki's trying to secure
more funds.

511
00:26:58.882 --> 00:27:00.667
All right. good.

512
00:27:02.930 --> 00:27:04.714
Whoa. whoa. whoa. whoa.
whoa. whoa. whoa.

513
00:27:04.845 --> 00:27:06.890
- What. what?
What is it?

514
00:27:07.021 --> 00:27:09.240
- The bar.
Have a look.

515
00:27:09.371 --> 00:27:11.373
Tall guy. big bushy beard.

516
00:27:13.723 --> 00:27:15.595
Yeah. yeah. I see him.

517
00:27:15.682 --> 00:27:17.771
That's Sasha Kotov.

518
00:27:17.858 --> 00:27:19.729
He's FSB.

519
00:27:20.948 --> 00:27:23.211
- Russian intelligence.
That's not a coincidence.

520
00:27:23.298 --> 00:27:25.300
No. it's not.

521
00:27:25.387 --> 00:27:26.606
He's either here with Mateo

522
00:27:26.693 --> 00:27:28.825
or he's trying
to buy the nuke himself.

523
00:27:28.912 --> 00:27:30.087
What. you think he has
something to do with

524
00:27:30.174 --> 00:27:31.088
Bill and Jonah missing?

525
00:27:31.132 --> 00:27:33.395
I wouldn't bet against it.

526
00:27:33.482 --> 00:27:35.397
Eliminate the other buyers.

527
00:27:35.484 --> 00:27:37.530
- Eliminate?
- Yeah.

528
00:27:37.573 --> 00:27:39.401
We need to find
Bill and Jonah now.

529
00:27:39.532 --> 00:27:40.968
OK. what about
the nuclear battery?

530
00:27:42.535 --> 00:27:43.579
Where was it written that

531
00:27:43.666 --> 00:27:46.190
two disasters can't hit
at the same time?

532
00:27:46.321 --> 00:27:47.975
Yeah. Colin. still nothing.

533
00:27:48.105 --> 00:27:50.499
OK. well. keep combing
security footage.

534
00:27:50.586 --> 00:27:51.848
let me know the second
you find anything.

535
00:27:51.935 --> 00:27:52.936
You got it.

536
00:27:52.980 --> 00:27:54.547
Zeeb have anything?

537
00:27:54.634 --> 00:27:56.200
Only that Bill and Jonah
never left the building.

538
00:27:56.331 --> 00:27:58.333
Apart from that...
- OK. well. that's good.

539
00:27:58.420 --> 00:28:00.291
Then we... we search room by room
until we find them.

540
00:28:00.378 --> 00:28:02.729
No. I mean. the second
we go and look for Bill.

541
00:28:02.816 --> 00:28:04.208
we lose eyes on Sasha.

542
00:28:04.295 --> 00:28:05.471
He could just walk out of here
with a nuke.

543
00:28:05.514 --> 00:28:07.995
Well then.
we divide and conquer.

544
00:28:08.082 --> 00:28:10.650
You go for Bill.
I'll distract Sasha at the bar.

545
00:28:10.737 --> 00:28:13.087
- No. no. Gina.
Sorry. no.

546
00:28:13.174 --> 00:28:14.392
- Yes.
- No.

547
00:28:14.436 --> 00:28:15.872
This guy's been FSB
for the last 20 years.

548
00:28:15.959 --> 00:28:17.961
- It's OK.
- He's a human lie detector.

549
00:28:18.092 --> 00:28:21.225
Stop treating me
like I'm going to break.

550
00:28:21.312 --> 00:28:23.880
I get it. you've been hurt.

551
00:28:24.011 --> 00:28:26.100
You lost someone.

552
00:28:26.230 --> 00:28:28.755
I'm not her.

553
00:28:28.842 --> 00:28:31.584
You know about Toni?

554
00:28:31.671 --> 00:28:33.847
- I'm a big girl. Colin.
I can do this.

555
00:28:38.808 --> 00:28:39.896
Zeeb?

556
00:28:39.983 --> 00:28:41.289
There's a whole bank of cameras

557
00:28:41.376 --> 00:28:42.595
covering the basement
storage area. B2.

558
00:28:42.725 --> 00:28:44.597
every one of them disabled.

559
00:28:44.684 --> 00:28:46.033
Well. that's not
a coincidence either.

560
00:28:46.120 --> 00:28:47.469
Thanks.

561
00:28:55.738 --> 00:28:58.698
If he makes you.
you walk away immediately.

562
00:28:58.785 --> 00:28:59.916
Yeah.

563
00:29:00.003 --> 00:29:01.831
Nikki's going to kill me.

564
00:29:01.875 --> 00:29:04.442
Well. we might all be
dead anyway. so there's that.

565
00:29:04.530 --> 00:29:06.836
Just...

566
00:29:06.923 --> 00:29:09.360
be careful. please.

567
00:29:09.447 --> 00:29:10.623
Promise.

568
00:29:30.718 --> 00:29:33.503
Drink menu. please.

569
00:29:33.590 --> 00:29:37.551
- Sable 6.
The best.

570
00:29:37.638 --> 00:29:39.770
- Oh.
All right then.

571
00:29:39.814 --> 00:29:42.034
I'll get that.
Thank you.

572
00:29:45.907 --> 00:29:48.257
You know. I had a boyfriend
from St. Petersburg.

573
00:29:48.388 --> 00:29:51.957
He loved Sable 6
a little too much.

574
00:29:52.044 --> 00:29:55.699
You. uh.
you spent time in Russia?

575
00:29:55.786 --> 00:29:57.397
Little bit.

576
00:29:57.484 --> 00:30:01.836
I have a love for the country.
The people. not so much.

577
00:30:01.923 --> 00:30:06.841
Ah. maybe I can. uh.
help you change your mind.

578
00:30:08.277 --> 00:30:12.281
You. uh. you visiting here?

579
00:30:12.368 --> 00:30:14.240
With anyone?

580
00:30:14.327 --> 00:30:17.243
I prefer to travel alone.
expect the unexpected.

581
00:30:17.286 --> 00:30:18.897
Ah. yes.

582
00:30:18.984 --> 00:30:21.595
American women
are so independent.

583
00:30:23.205 --> 00:30:25.251
So confident.

584
00:30:25.294 --> 00:30:29.646
And we're open books.
unlike you. a man...

585
00:30:29.733 --> 00:30:33.824
shrouded in mystery.
- Yeah?

586
00:30:33.912 --> 00:30:36.218
What would you like to know?
Huh?

587
00:30:36.305 --> 00:30:38.481
Hmm.

588
00:31:13.516 --> 00:31:15.388
I've always loved tigers.

589
00:31:15.518 --> 00:31:18.130
Independent. strong hunters.

590
00:31:18.173 --> 00:31:19.958
They work in the shadows.

591
00:31:20.088 --> 00:31:21.176
Suits you.

592
00:31:21.307 --> 00:31:23.135
- Yeah?
- Mm-hmm.

593
00:31:23.222 --> 00:31:25.311
So you got me
all figured out. huh?

594
00:31:25.398 --> 00:31:29.010
Well. I can take a guess.

595
00:31:29.097 --> 00:31:31.317
You're a Russian oligarch.

596
00:31:31.360 --> 00:31:33.275
Here for business
with your mistress.

597
00:31:33.362 --> 00:31:35.886
You brought along
a couple scary men

598
00:31:35.930 --> 00:31:38.193
to keep you company.

599
00:31:38.280 --> 00:31:40.717
Does that sound about right?

600
00:31:40.804 --> 00:31:42.154
No mistress tonight.

601
00:31:42.284 --> 00:31:43.851
Oh.

602
00:31:43.938 --> 00:31:46.245
Well. you don't need
any protection from me.

603
00:31:46.332 --> 00:31:48.769
- Perhaps not.
- Mm.

604
00:31:48.856 --> 00:31:54.296
Perhaps we continue
our conversation in private?

605
00:31:55.863 --> 00:31:57.778
Maybe after
a couple more of these.

606
00:31:57.821 --> 00:32:02.043
Ouch. you find me
so unattractive.

607
00:32:02.130 --> 00:32:04.437
You find me so easy?

608
00:32:07.396 --> 00:32:08.919
No. I'm just meeting up
with a friend.

609
00:32:09.007 --> 00:32:11.661
and I don't want to be rude.
make him wait.

610
00:32:14.012 --> 00:32:16.362
Ah.

611
00:32:16.449 --> 00:32:18.842
I thought you said
you were traveling alone.

612
00:32:20.409 --> 00:32:21.671
I am.

613
00:32:21.802 --> 00:32:24.196
We ran into each other
in the lobby.

614
00:32:24.326 --> 00:32:28.461
- Mm.
- Mm.

615
00:32:28.591 --> 00:32:32.856
Excuse me a second while
I run to the ladies room?

616
00:32:32.943 --> 00:32:35.076
You're not going anywhere

617
00:32:35.163 --> 00:32:39.254
until I find out
exactly who you are.

618
00:33:49.368 --> 00:33:51.239
Jeez. you two look like
you've been having fun.

619
00:33:51.326 --> 00:33:53.328
We've been
getting to know each other.

620
00:33:53.459 --> 00:33:55.765
- Where's Gina?
- She's running interference.

621
00:33:55.896 --> 00:33:58.072
We gotta get upstairs
and make Mateo an offer.

622
00:33:58.159 --> 00:33:59.508
I did while
you two were down here

623
00:33:59.595 --> 00:34:01.206
braiding each other's hair.
- What. we got the nuke?

624
00:34:01.292 --> 00:34:03.031
No. there's other buyers.

625
00:34:03.120 --> 00:34:05.253
Oh. let me guess.
our new Russian friend?

626
00:34:05.340 --> 00:34:06.907
Sasha Kotov. he's FSB.

627
00:34:06.994 --> 00:34:08.648
- That's not good.
- No. it's exactly what I said.

628
00:34:08.735 --> 00:34:10.084
We need to get to Mateo's suite

629
00:34:10.171 --> 00:34:11.693
and try and close this deal
before anyone else.

630
00:34:11.780 --> 00:34:13.347
Here.
Guns go first.

631
00:34:20.963 --> 00:34:23.532
Don't...

632
00:34:30.235 --> 00:34:32.672
- Oh. yeah. man.
You like the rush.

633
00:34:32.759 --> 00:34:34.063
Let's move.

634
00:34:34.152 --> 00:34:36.979
Yeah. clean yourself up
before you meet your public.

635
00:34:37.067 --> 00:34:38.894
I have my best people on this.

636
00:34:38.980 --> 00:34:40.375
Rest assured
we'll bring the device in.

637
00:34:40.506 --> 00:34:42.508
That might not be possible.

638
00:34:42.594 --> 00:34:44.204
Oh. what does that mean?

639
00:34:44.291 --> 00:34:46.903
CSA finished examining
the debris field.

640
00:34:46.989 --> 00:34:50.037
They confirm the satellite is
Russian. but more important.

641
00:34:50.167 --> 00:34:52.039
they analyzed the samples
for radiation.

642
00:34:52.125 --> 00:34:54.346
Positive for radionuclides.

643
00:34:54.476 --> 00:34:56.260
- Get to the point.
What are you telling me?

644
00:34:56.391 --> 00:34:58.350
All the tests indicate
this thing is leaking.

645
00:34:58.437 --> 00:35:00.830
Well. what does that mean
for my guys?

646
00:35:00.916 --> 00:35:03.529
It means they can't get close
for any extended period of time

647
00:35:03.615 --> 00:35:06.009
or they'll be breathing in
radioactive particles.

648
00:35:06.140 --> 00:35:07.533
It's a death sentence.

649
00:35:07.620 --> 00:35:09.361
Oh. and here's the real danger.

650
00:35:09.447 --> 00:35:11.145
Oh. a death sentence
wasn't the real danger?

651
00:35:11.276 --> 00:35:12.407
Based on our modeling.

652
00:35:12.538 --> 00:35:15.149
this thing could blow
at any minute.

653
00:35:15.280 --> 00:35:16.281
OK.

654
00:35:18.038 --> 00:35:19.300
That's radiation poisoning.

655
00:35:19.387 --> 00:35:21.172
Certainly looks like it.

656
00:35:24.305 --> 00:35:26.394
Nikki.

657
00:35:26.438 --> 00:35:28.396
Colin. the nuke is leaking.

658
00:35:28.484 --> 00:35:30.311
Yeah. we're aware.

659
00:35:30.442 --> 00:35:32.226
- What?
How... are you...

660
00:35:32.313 --> 00:35:34.490
Either that or Mateo
had a serious nut allergy.

661
00:35:34.577 --> 00:35:35.708
He's dead.

662
00:35:35.839 --> 00:35:37.797
He must have had the nuke
on him this entire time.

663
00:35:37.884 --> 00:35:40.104
That's what.
three days' direct exposure?

664
00:35:40.234 --> 00:35:41.627
- Yeah.
No wonder.

665
00:35:41.714 --> 00:35:43.324
- Well. What about the nuke?
Have you found it?

666
00:35:43.455 --> 00:35:44.761
No. no. we've looked everywhere.

667
00:35:44.848 --> 00:35:46.110
It's not here.

668
00:35:46.197 --> 00:35:49.374
- Whoa. jeez.
- You.

669
00:35:49.505 --> 00:35:51.898
We checked his pulse.

670
00:35:52.029 --> 00:35:54.684
Mateo. where's the nuke?

671
00:35:54.771 --> 00:35:57.077
Sasha took the nuke.

672
00:35:57.164 --> 00:35:59.950
And he has the girl.

673
00:36:00.037 --> 00:36:01.995
He know she's CIA.

674
00:36:07.305 --> 00:36:09.394
Guys. the NEST team
is on the way to you.

675
00:36:09.525 --> 00:36:12.179
Where's Gina?
- Uh. yeah. Nikki. gotta go.

676
00:36:12.310 --> 00:36:13.877
Lot of moving pieces.
but we're on it.

677
00:36:15.661 --> 00:36:18.272
Let's go.

678
00:36:22.407 --> 00:36:24.322
NEST team's almost here.

679
00:36:26.498 --> 00:36:29.153
That's her.

680
00:36:29.283 --> 00:36:31.068
And that's got to be the nuke.

681
00:36:31.155 --> 00:36:32.156
Stay here.

682
00:36:32.286 --> 00:36:35.333
Yeah. uh. you kids have fun.

683
00:36:35.420 --> 00:36:36.726
- So what's your plan?
You're going to kill me now?

684
00:36:36.856 --> 00:36:38.162
Oh. no. no. no. no. no.

685
00:36:38.249 --> 00:36:40.164
You're going to die
in a field in Russia

686
00:36:40.251 --> 00:36:41.557
after we get everything we want

687
00:36:41.687 --> 00:36:43.602
from that pretty
little head of yours.

688
00:36:48.738 --> 00:36:50.087
The Russians sent you
to collect their fallen tech.

689
00:36:50.174 --> 00:36:51.567
but you're never
going to get it back.

690
00:36:51.654 --> 00:36:53.438
It's going to melt.
radiation is going to spread.

691
00:36:53.525 --> 00:36:55.440
and millions will be exposed.

692
00:36:55.527 --> 00:36:57.094
NEST team. are you in position?

693
00:36:57.224 --> 00:36:58.356
- Yes. sir.
Call it.

694
00:37:00.924 --> 00:37:03.143
I'm not getting in there
with that thing.

695
00:37:03.230 --> 00:37:04.928
Take them.

696
00:37:17.331 --> 00:37:19.246
Get out.

697
00:37:39.571 --> 00:37:42.052
- Secure him.
- Let's go.

698
00:37:43.357 --> 00:37:44.620
You OK?

699
00:37:44.663 --> 00:37:45.838
- Yeah. I'm good.
- Yeah?

700
00:37:45.925 --> 00:37:46.796
This nuke's going to melt
any minute.

701
00:37:46.926 --> 00:37:48.406
Then we need
to evacuate everyone now.

702
00:37:48.493 --> 00:37:50.843
- What? No.
There's no time.

703
00:37:50.887 --> 00:37:52.715
If it melts down during evac.
we're all dead anyway.

704
00:37:52.845 --> 00:37:54.717
No. we need to
get it out of here.

705
00:37:54.804 --> 00:37:56.544
Yeah.

706
00:37:56.632 --> 00:37:59.809
Passed a quarry two miles back.

707
00:37:59.896 --> 00:38:02.812
I could get this thing
underground.

708
00:38:02.942 --> 00:38:06.206
Jonah. you don't have
to be a hero. man.

709
00:38:06.293 --> 00:38:11.821
- Why not?
For the first time in my life.

710
00:38:11.951 --> 00:38:14.214
Go home.

711
00:38:14.301 --> 00:38:15.694
See your girl.

712
00:39:18.844 --> 00:39:20.454
Contact Headquarters.

713
00:39:20.541 --> 00:39:24.850
Make sure we debrief them on
all the radiation containment.

714
00:39:41.867 --> 00:39:45.610
I'd. uh. offer
to buy you a drink. but...

715
00:39:45.741 --> 00:39:47.481
But I've had enough vodka
for at least a year?

716
00:39:47.612 --> 00:39:50.180
Yeah.

717
00:39:50.267 --> 00:39:52.835
Look. with Sasha.
that was my call to put you in.

718
00:39:52.922 --> 00:39:54.140
I never should have done that.

719
00:39:54.271 --> 00:39:56.403
No. I know what I signed up for.

720
00:39:56.490 --> 00:39:59.929
Danger is part of the job.

721
00:40:00.016 --> 00:40:02.540
Well. for what it's worth.
you did quite well.

722
00:40:02.583 --> 00:40:05.412
Definitely. uh. trending
in the right direction.

723
00:40:05.499 --> 00:40:08.807
But. uh. more importantly.

724
00:40:08.894 --> 00:40:11.114
what are we going to tell Nikki?

725
00:40:11.201 --> 00:40:13.420
'Cause we need
to get our stories straight.

726
00:40:34.485 --> 00:40:35.834
Hey.

727
00:40:37.227 --> 00:40:38.924
You're home.

728
00:40:39.011 --> 00:40:41.100
- Yeah. sorry.
Go back to sleep.

729
00:40:41.187 --> 00:40:43.450
Good day?

730
00:40:43.537 --> 00:40:45.844
Yeah. just long.

731
00:40:45.931 --> 00:40:47.106
I'm gonna shower.

732
00:40:47.193 --> 00:40:51.284
- OK.
I love you.

733
00:40:51.371 --> 00:40:52.720
Love you too.

734
00:41:11.244 --> 00:41:14.244
- -

735
00:41:31.534 --> 00:41:34.534
- -

736
00:41:45.258 --> 00:41:48.258
- -
